HEADWORD: Termagancy
<hw>Ter"ma*gan*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being termagant; turbulence; tumultuousness; <as>as, a violent
<ex>termagancy</ex> of temper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

